It would be great if the user could have an option to change the order and see the comments like in JIRA, with the new information on the bottom and the old info on the top.

h3. Steps to reproduce

# In JIRA, grant only "Browse Project" permissions to one user;
# Login with this user;
# Access this project's Service Desk through JIRA with this user;

h3. Current behaviour

You will verify that the user has the ability of viewing SLA and Reports configurations.

h3. Expected behaviour

Even thought he can't edit them, he shouldn't be able to view these configs at all.

Observations: This isn't actually a bug, but it also isn't a new feature, it's an improvement request but I couldn't find this issue type in the system.

Also, this doesn't fit in [JSD-40|https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSD-40] because JSD-40 intends to restrict the access to the user only to Service Desk. This specific ticket allows the user to access Service Desk and JIRA, but only restrict the access to Service Desk's configuration through JIRA.

