Currently, the SLA measurement only applicable per individual issue basis, it would better if we can offer SLA time tracking to keep track of the time spend for each group (time that they spend on issue before transferring to another group)

h5. Customer justification/use case scenario:
{quote}
Need for SLA tracking based on assignee group of an issue:-
As I mentioned in my previous comments a single issue would be assigned to different groups. Ideally an issue reported from customer is handled by operators who create the issue in tool. They transfer this issue to support team. 

Support team has different levels *L1*, *L2* and *L3*. Life cycle starts with L1 support team and they can do some analysis, task retries, add more information and pass to next level (if the issue is not solved). Next level support team has more access to production environment and they can do changes to database/files for fixing the problem. 

Similar to first level, second level team also adds more information and pass to next level. Third level deals with program fixes. They correct programs and redeploy it in different environments. We have different SLAs for these support levels based on the priority of issue
{quote}

